caption: Great food and atmosphere! Family-friendly but nice for a datenight, too.
Tried the shrimp and the fish tacos. Both were excellent and very substantial.
The food was great and the drinks were delicious. Service could be a little bit better but that's just me. Overall great experience
Really solid Mexican food, in the opinion of someone who has never been to Mexico. Everything was fresh and had lots of flavor. Can't wait to order again!
Delicious food!

Best Mexican food I’ve had in Brooklyn. They do the Americanized stuff like burritos really well but their tinga is particularly good. Super nice staff, free chips and salsa with your order. Recommend the enchiladas (both kinds), burritos, crispy tinga tostadas. Chorizo tacos also good. Good prices.
The homemade chips here are incredible. The veggie burrito was too dry, but I liked the enchilada plate and would come back for that.
My go-to for Mexican food in Cobble/Boerum Hill. The chips are perfectly crispy and fresh. Their fajitas and tacos (with house made tortillas) are must-tries.
Shrimp quesadilla is the best quesadilla you'll ever taste
The food is excellent !
Amazing fish tacos and great service

My fav spot for quality mexican food. Super place to meet and chat with coworkers. The staff was very helpful and welcoming. This place has a great feel to it. Feels like a place in Los Angeles I loved.
great service

I've had delivery or carry out from Purepecha about a dozen times since in-person dining has been on hold, and have been happy with my meal every time.  Favorites are the vegan fajitas and the ground beef tacos.
We were excited to try this but the grilled chicken tasted burnt and there wasn’t any sauce on the enchiladas.
Just like the food I ate when I was in medical school in Tampico Mexico! Loved it
This spot is worth a try. They have large portions for convenient rates. Consistently clean and with good character. Would recommend to others.
This place is one of my favorites! Reasonable rates, large dishes and the staff members are always friendly.
Your carnitas gives me great joy in my life. I have to hold back from ordering everyday. Xoxo, your biggest fan

The food is well done, creative, and prices are fair when you recieve the quality of service. Just my opinion on the prices. Nachos are addictive as well as the burritos. Full to where I won't need dinner after lunch. Incredible spot.
The best restaurant, thank you brother Kevin you doing great!!

food never showed up and then they cancelled the order when they were so late....i called and they said the delivery guy was going to bring it on his next trip...i waited over 2 hours and 45 minutes before a received an email cancellation...BEWARE!!!!
Amazing environment and very welcoming service. The meals were crisp and delightful. Will absolutely recommend this place to anyone. Convenient rates and large portions. Keep up the great work.
Pretty good!
Excellent service and the coffee is delicious. Ordered steak and eggs for brunch and left feeling unsatisfied. The steak was so good (pounded skirt) but oh so small. I finished it off in 8 bites.
I always stop grabbing some food here. I love the quick customer service and well prepared dishes. I recommend this place.
Food is amazing....
Highly recomended.
Food is amazing. Everything clearly fresh and made there. Will be back!
Really good food generally, amazing nachos. Great margherita! The chicken in the fajitas was a weird texture though, which lost the meal a star.
Nice place to eat.....service is good especially bartender named Daniel.....
Good food good service
Terrific, all around. Definitely call ahead for take out and not on a busy night.
Authentic Mexican food. Friendly staff.

Some of the best tacos and corn tortillas I've had in NYC. The tortillas held up even when soaked in the meat's juices and the meat itself was delicious. Service was friendly and welcoming. Just sat at the bar and felt like a regular. Can't recommend this enough.

Honestly, it was fine. The food tasted ok, but the service was completely nonexistent, the food came out at different times, and when my friend’s food did come out it was cold. I was bummed out because I really wanted to like this place!

Service was really nice here. They weren't the best buttermilk pancakes I've had in the neighbourhood but they did taste well. My husband loved them though. The place is bright and cozy. Sports playing by the bar, so could work for a nice sit down or hang out.
Authentic local mexican spot
Let's just hope it survives.  It's a great add to the neighborhood.
Poor service.
Excellent mexican food, same as in mexico
Excellent vegetarian burrito!
Everything was so good and the owners are incredibly nice. Lucky to have this spot in our neighborhood.
Very cute and warm atmosphere. Perfect brunch spot. Delicious Mexican fare

Terrible customer experience from them. Ordered delivery, food never came, was assured driver was on the way, tried contacting restaurant 5 times after and no answer. Completely ghosted.  UPDATE: food finally came 2.5 hrs later after the restuarant had already closed.
Excellent service
Friendly service, fresh made tortillas and great margs! Wonderful addition to the neighborhood!
Was here for brunch. Pretty lackluster food. Had the chorizo burrito which was pretty bean heavy and chilequiles were too soggy. Good service.
Brunch was great. Avocado toast with poached eggs, very tasty. Avocado was mashed and had diced tomatoes, poached eggs on top on seven grain toast. Delicious will definitely come back😋😊
Great food!  Good service, nice atmosphere!!

Craving Mexican? This is one of the best options in the neighborhood. I gave up on Fatty Daddy, and Fast and Fresh Burrito (EXCELLENT) can be a little far away. good food, quick and friendly service. I highly recommend the Burrito smothered in pork sauce . WOW. The huge pieces of pork shoulder in the sauce could be a meal unto themselves. The quesadillas are also great.
The food here is incredible, all of it, I haven't had something here that I did not absolutely love. Try it, you will not be sorry, you will thank me

Though I’ve walked past Purepecha a few times, my first experience was with delivery, which was surprisingly quick. We ordered beef and tinga tacos with guacamole - all of the above were flavorful and fresh. A great addition to the neighborhood, can’t wait to dine in next!
Good food reasonable prices, nice decor. Should definitely give it a chance if you're in the area.

I’m speaking as a Mexican raised between South Texas and Mexico- this place is really great. Food was so delicately flavorful and the service was nice and efficient. I got the carne Asada platter and loved the taste and quality of everything on the plate.  update: I have returned and also ordered delivery and I stand by my review above and then some. Plus, the tortillas were so good I almost cried.
the first time it was much better now I didn't like it

This is place has been open for 3 weeks. There's no liquor license yet so they're currently BYOB. The guac, chips and salsa were very good. Quesadillas were good too. My friend enjoyed her steak tacos and I liked my fish tacos ok. I thought the churros were okay too. We were the only table there when we arrived at opening and service was friendly and quick. As they filled up service got slower.
Awesome authentic Mexican food, really nice addition to the neighborhood.
The carnitas are legit
Absolutely amazing meal that didn’t let me down .  Rvteddyp
Love the hand made fresh tortillas

My boyfriend and I were strolling along Smith St. and searching for a nice place for a quick bite to eat. We stumbled upon Purépecha Mexican Restaurant and the menu looked pretty enticing. I'm assuming we came at a bad time because the host was sitting down eating and grabbed the pitcher of water that was next to her and placed it on our table (which had many flies by the way). We managed to get pass that and decided to give it a try in spite of. My boyfriend ordered the quesadillas and I ordered Tinga tacos. Each of our dishes were bland, tasteless and undercooked to say the least. Granted we were the only patrons in the restaurant, however that doesn't excuse the subpar service and experience.
